  <bioghist id="aspace_cba35ca604ce94a2a7ffb672356602cb">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Transgender activist and 2006 Cornell English Ph.D., Juang was a leader in organizing Cornell's first transgender conference, TransPositions, that took place on March 27-29, 1998.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_c1c260856d4b0a4161a3545607a34a98">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Materials related to trans activism and Asian American, queer, and transgender identities, including correspondence and materials related to a 2001 Transgender Law and Policy Roundtable sponsored by the Center for Lesbian and Gay Studies (CLAGS) of the City University of New York.</p>  </scopecontent>
